    <br/>

    <table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center">
    <tr>
        <td bgcolor="#bbbbbb" width="1%" nowrap align="center">
            &nbsp;<font color="#ffffff"><b>Description</b></font>&nbsp;
        </td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
    </tr>
    </table>

    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p>We noticed some primary surgery site values across the 4 enriched cohorts weren’t yet mapped in the definitive_surgery_prioritization tab of the <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1_2rAbT5obq_GbN4Dh1SciXf6QkidftFb0rM6rxxpz10/edit?usp=sharing" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">ADS DD</a>, which is called into syhelpr for use in the primary_site_surgery.R functions via the definitions.R functions. We need to identify any missing codes and add them to our prioritization list.</p>

<p>Specifically, we need to:</p>

<ol>
	<li>In each enriched cohort, look for any <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/101qGNNdkoB-7QLH482IDsWPWNUWpq0qkZgrkRCOacbg/edit?gid=0#gid=0" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">descriptions</a> that haven’t yet been mapped/ranked in the <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1_2rAbT5obq_GbN4Dh1SciXf6QkidftFb0rM6rxxpz10/edit?usp=sharing" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">ADS DD</a>.  → <em>Basically, pull all unique primary site surgery descriptions for each cohort, and look for any not yet found in the ADS DD’s definitive_surgery_prioritization tab mapping.</em></li>
	<li>Discuss with Epi to determine the mapping and ranks of these missing descriptions, and update the definitive_surgery_prioritization tab of the DD.</li>
	<li>Run <a href="https://github.com/syapse/syhelper-package/blob/master/data-raw/map_surgery_crosswalk.R" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">syhelpr</a> to update the mappings found in ca.map_surgery_crosswalk using the <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/101qGNNdkoB-7QLH482IDsWPWNUWpq0qkZgrkRCOacbg/edit?gid=0#gid=0" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">v2 (flexibility)</a> tab of Master Surgery Crosswalk google sheet, as well as uncomment + run the definitions.R file code, which pulls directly from the ADS DD’s <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1_2rAbT5obq_GbN4Dh1SciXf6QkidftFb0rM6rxxpz10/edit?gid=1562226994#gid=1562226994" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">definitive_surgery_prioritization</a> tab.</li>
	<li>Check for any changes to the values for primary_site_surgery and definitive_surgery fields in the 4 enriched ADS. → <em>No R changes to these cohorts are necessary; the mapping is automated via syhelpr’s ingestion of the ADS DD, so just run the 4 cohorts before and after the changes to check for how many patients' were affected by this updated mapping.</em></li>
</ol>




<p>Variables involved:</p>

<ul>
	<li>rxsummsurgprimsite (both registry and OC prior to 2023)</li>
	<li>rxsummsurgprimsite2023 (registry only for 2023+)</li>
	<li>rxhospsurgprimsite2023 (OC only for 2023+)</li>
</ul>




<hr />

<p>Archive</p>

<p>Surgery prioritizations need to be updated after new and old primary site surgery variables have been harmonized by CI map &#8211; can also remove code work around in definitive surgery code once updated-.</p>

<p>While working on <a href="https://n-power.atlassian.net/browse/SYR-111" title="smart-link" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://n-power.atlassian.net/browse/SYR-111</a>, I realized that the surgery codes 12, 13, 15, 19, 23, and 24 were missing from <tt>ca.map_definitive_surgery_prioritization</tt> for the lung cohort. We should add these and check to see if any others are missing.</p>
            <br/>
        </td>
    </tr>
    </table>

